notesStmt.note: Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: A daily prayer book, according to the Provencal (Avignon) rite.

msItem.title: Prayers for Rosh ha-Shanah and Yom Kipur
Services for the night of Simḥat Torah

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 ; ruled lines: 14; written lines: 13; Uniform layout. Visible pricking and hard-point ruling. Hair side and flesh side distinguishable. Initial words written in larger characters. Leaf catchwords on every verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Ashkenazi (French) semi-cursive script, punctuated, of the 14th century.

binding.p: Post-1600. Black buckram. Gold tooled. Spine: 'Prayer Book. Rite of Carpentras. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 19,667.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Adolphus Asher (b. 1800, d. 1853), Berlin bookseller and dealer to the British Museum 1841-1853: purchased from him by the British Museum on 12 November 1853: inscribed, folio [286v].
